

Java 11 Features (Interview Important + Examples)

Java 11 is a Long-Term Support (LTS) version and is widely used in enterprise + Spring Boot applications.

1. HttpClient API ⭐ (Most Important)
...........................................
Java 11 introduced a modern HTTP client to replace HttpURLConnection.

Example – GET Request
import java.net.URI;
import java.net.http.*;

public class HttpClientExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {

        HttpClient client =
                HttpClient.newHttpClient();

        HttpRequest request =
                HttpRequest.newBuilder()
                        .uri(URI.create(
                            "https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts/1"))
                        .build();

        HttpResponse<String> response =
                client.send(request,
                        HttpResponse.BodyHandlers.ofString());

        System.out.println(response.body());
    }
}
Async Example
client.sendAsync(request,
        HttpResponse.BodyHandlers.ofString())
      .thenApply(HttpResponse::body)
      .thenAccept(System.out::println);
Benefits

✔ Supports HTTP/2
✔ Async + Non-blocking calls
✔ Cleaner API
✔ Replaces old HttpURLConnection

2. String API Improvements ⭐
............................................
Java 11 added useful methods in String.

Example
public class StringExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        String str = "  Java 11  ";

        System.out.println(str.isBlank());
        System.out.println(str.strip());
        System.out.println(str.repeat(3));
    }
}
